children.label: MySQL
children.description: A powerful MySQL integration plugin that provides comprehensive database connectivity. Features include table/view management, data import/export, SQL query execution, stored procedure support, and real-time data synchronization. Optimized for high-performance data operations with connection pooling and batch processing capabilities.
children.author: datacap-community

children.label: ClickHouse
children.description: ClickHouse is a distributed column-oriented database. It is a distributed database with a focus on performance, scalability, and ease of use.
children.author: datacap-community

children.label: Influxdb
children.description: InfluxDB is a time series database that stores and retrieves data points. It is a distributed database with a focus on performance, scalability, and ease of use.
children.author: datacap-community

children.label: Apache Solr
children.description: Solr is highly reliable, scalable and fault tolerant, providing distributed indexing, replication and load-balanced querying, automated failover and recovery, centralized configuration and more. Solr powers the search and navigation features of many of the world's largest internet sites.
children.author: datacap-community

children.label: CrateDB
children.description: CrateDB is a hyper-fast database for real-time analytics and hybrid search. It handles multiple types of data and combines the simplicity of SQL with the scalability of a distributed architecture.
children.author: datacap-community

children.label: Apache Zookeeper
children.description: Zookeeper is a distributed, distributed configuration service. It is a distributed database with a focus on performance, scalability, and ease of use.
children.author: datacap-community

children.label: Apache Kafka
children.description: Apache Kafka is an open-source distributed event streaming platform used by thousands of companies for high-performance data pipelines, streaming analytics, data integration, and mission-critical applications.
children.author: datacap-community

children.label: Redis
children.description: Redis is an in-memory data store used by millions of developers as a cache, vector database, document database, streaming engine, and message broker. Redis has built-in replication and different levels of on-disk persistence. It supports complex data types (for example, strings, hashes, lists, sets, sorted sets, and JSON), with atomic operations defined on those data types.
children.author: datacap-community

children.label: H2
children.description: H2 is a small, fast, and easy-to-use in-memory database.
children.author: datacap-community

children.label: DB2
children.description: IBM® Db2® is the cloud-native database built to power low-latency transactions, real-time analytics and AI applications at scale.
children.author: datacap-community

children.label: Dameng
children.description: A professional database software developer and service provider, we provide users with technically advanced and detailed products.
children.author: datacap-community

children.label: Apache HDFS
children.description: Hadoop Distributed File System (HDFS) is a distributed file system based on the Hadoop project.
children.author: datacap-community

children.label: Ali OSS
children.description: Ali OSS is a cloud storage service that provides a simple, secure and efficient way to store and manage data.
children.author: datacap-community

children.label: Dremio
children.description: Dremio is a free, open source, distributed data platform.
children.author: datacap-community

children.label: Apache Druid
children.description: A high performance, real-time analytics database that delivers sub-second queries on streaming and batch data at scale and under load.
children.author: datacap-community

children.label: DuckDB
children.description: To use DuckDB, you must first create a connection to a database. The exact syntax varies between the client APIs but it typically involves passing an argument to configure persistence.
children.author: datacap-community

children.label: Apache Pinot
children.description: Apache Pinot is a real-time distributed OLAP datastore, built to deliver scalable real-time analytics with low latency. It can ingest from batch data sources (such as Hadoop HDFS, Amazon S3, Azure ADLS, Google Cloud Storage) as well as stream data sources (such as Apache Kafka).
children.author: datacap-community

children.label: Apache Cassandra
children.description: Cassandra is a distributed key-value store for the cloud.
children.author: datacap-community

children.label: MatrixOne
children.description: MatrixOne is a hyper-converged cloud & edge native distributed database with a structure that separates storage, computation, and transactions to form a consolidated HSTAP data engine. This engine enables a single database system to accommodate diverse business loads such as OLTP, OLAP, and stream computing. It also supports deployment and utilization across public, private, and edge clouds, ensuring compatibility with diverse infrastructures.
children.author: datacap-community

children.label: ScyllaDB
children.description: ScyllaDB is a distributed database written in C++ and designed to fully exploit modern cloud infrastructure. It utilizes a shard-per-core architecture, meaning each CPU core has dedicated resources that independently handle data for maximum efficiency.
children.author: datacap-community

children.label: ParadeDB
children.description: ParadeDB is a modern Elasticsearch alternative built on Postgres. Built for real-time, update-heavy workloads.
children.author: datacap-community

children.label: Apache Hive 2.x
children.description: The Apache Hive ™ is a distributed, fault-tolerant data warehouse system that enables analytics at a massive scale and facilitates reading, writing, and managing petabytes of data residing in distributed storage using SQL.
children.author: datacap-community

children.label: Apache Kyuubi
children.description: Apache Kyuubi, a distributed and multi-tenant gateway to provide serverless SQL on lakehouses.
children.author: datacap-community

children.label: Apache Ignite
children.description: Apache Ignite is a distributed database for high-performance computing with in-memory speed.
children.author: datacap-community

children.label: Apache Impala
children.description: Apache Impala is the open source, native analytic database for open data and table formats.
children.author: datacap-community

children.label: Apache Kylin
children.description: Apache Kylin is a leading open source OLAP engine for Big Data capable for sub-second query latency on trillions of records. Since being created and open sourced by eBay in 2014, and graduated to Top Level Project of Apache Software Foundation in 2015. Kylin has quickly been adopted by thousands of organizations world widely as their critical analytics application for Big Data.
